Interface COM Port: Select which serial port the extender is connected to.
Connect: Opens the COM port for communication to the extender
Update Software: Selection becomes available after the extender is detected. Once selected, the extender will be programmed.
Read Software: Selection becomes available after the extender is detected. Once selected, the extender current software version will be reported.
Connecting To The Extender With the extender connected to the cable, and the cable connected to the computer, start the ExpressLink application and connect to the COM port assigned to the cable. When you press the connect button, the application will wait for you to apply power to the extender. Power the extender, and observe the notification bar at the bottom of the application. If the application says "Bootloader detected" than the extender is connected properly.
Instructions for Upgrading Software Apply power to the unit to enter bootloader mode. Press the "Update Software" button. A status bar on the bottom left shows the progress. When the extender is finished programming, you can disconnect the extender, and reprogram another.
Instructions for Reading Current Software Apply power to the unit to enter bootloader mode. Press the "Read Software" button. The software currently programmed to the extender will be displayed on the bottom left hand corner of the application.
Contacting Technical Support http://icron.com/support Tel: 1-604-638-3920
Please include the following information with your technical support request: • Part number and serial number of both LEX (local extender) and REX (remote extender) • Host computer make and model • Operating System installed (e.g. Windows XP, Mac OS X, etc.) • Make and model of any USB device(s) attached to the LEX and REX • Description of the installation • Description of the problem
